\begin{verbatim}
FDFit(window)
\end{verbatim}
Finite difference fit for modal density estimation

\textbf{Field}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{window::Int}: Parameter is the number of modes to consider in the finite difference approximation (default is 5)

\end{itemize}

\begin{verbatim}
PolyFit()
\end{verbatim}
Third-order polynomial fit for modal density estimation

\begin{verbatim}
Lowess(window)
\end{verbatim}
Lowess (Local Weighted Scatterplot Smoothing) method for modal density estimation

\textbf{Field}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{window::Float64}: Fraction of modes to consider in the local regression (default is 0.3)

\end{itemize}

\begin{verbatim}
CSFit()
\end{verbatim}
Cubic spline interpolation method for modal density estimation

\begin{verbatim}
modal_density(frequencies, method::FDFit)
modal_density(frequencies, method::PolyFit)
modal_density(frequencies, method::Lowess)
modal_density(frequencies, method::CSFit)
\end{verbatim}
Compute the modal density of a structure from the knowledge of its resonance frequencies using different methods

\textbf{Inputs}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{frequencies::Vector\{Real\}}: Vector of resonance frequencies


\item \texttt{method}: Method to use for modal density estimation

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{FDFit}: Finite difference fitting method


\item \texttt{PolyFit}: Third order polynomial global fitting method


\item \texttt{Lowess}: Lowess method


\item \texttt{CSFit}: Cubic spline interpolation method

\end{itemize}
\end{itemize}
\textbf{Outputs}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{md::Vector\{Real\}}: Modal density values corresponding to the input frequencies


\item \texttt{freqs::Vector\{Real\}}: Sorted frequencies corresponding to the modal density values

\end{itemize}
